The World Bank has trained 79 Federal and State government officials on how to manage the intervention of the Community and Social Development Project, Additional Financing (CSDP AF). The project is targeted at gender and vulnerable people, internally displaced persons and poor people in communities across the country. Issues discussed include sensitization of the vulnerable groups, proper targeting of the groups for intervention, said a statement by Suleiman Odapu, Information and Communication Officer, CSDP AF.Â  Speaking at the opening of the two-day training, World Bank Task Team Leader for CSDP AF, Professor Foluso Okunmadewa advised CSDP State Agencies not to compromise on the use of state government approved Poverty Map.